  "prompt": "Which optional subjects can I choose for the IAS exam?",
  "response": "For the IAS (Indian Administrative Service) exam, which is part of the **UPSC Civil Services Examination (CSE)**, you can choose one optional subject from a list of **26 subjects** provided by the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC). The optional subject carries **500 marks** (250 marks for Paper I and 250 marks for Paper II) in the **Mains** stage of the exam.\n\nHere\u2019s the list of optional subjects for the IAS exam:\n\n1. **Agriculture**\n2. **Animal Husbandry and Veterinary Science**\n3. **Anthropology**\n4. **Botany**\n5. **Chemistry**\n6. **Civil Engineering**\n7. **Commerce and Accountancy**\n8. **Economics**\n9. **Electrical Engineering**\n10. **Geography**\n11. **Geology**\n12. **History**\n13. **Law**\n14. **Management**\n15. **Mathematics**\n16. **Mechanical Engineering**\n17. **Medical Science**\n18. **Philosophy**\n19. **Physics**\n20. **Political Science and International Relations**\n21. **Psychology**\n22. **Public Administration**\n23. **Sociology**\n24. **Statistics**\n25. **Zoology**\n26. **Literature of any one of the following languages:**  \n   - Assamese  \n   - Bengali  \n   - Bodo  \n   - Dogri  \n   - Gujarati  \n   - Hindi  \n   - Kannada  \n   - Kashmiri  \n   - Konkani  \n   - Maithili  \n   - Malayalam  \n   - Manipuri  \n   - Marathi  \n   - Nepali  \n   - Odia  \n   - Punjabi  \n   - Sanskrit  \n   - Santhali  \n   - Sindhi  \n   - Tamil  \n   - Telugu  \n   - Urdu  \n\n### Tips for Choosing an Optional Subject:\n1. **Interest and Background:** Choose a subject you are genuinely interested in or have a background in.\n2. **Overlap with GS Syllabus:** Some subjects like **Geography**, **History**, **Public Administration**, **Sociology**, and **Political Science** overlap with the General Studies (GS) syllabus, which can be advantageous.\n3. **Availability of Resources:** Ensure that study material and guidance are readily available for the subject.\n4. **Scoring Potential:** Some subjects are known to be scoring if prepared well, such as **Public Administration**, **Sociology**, and **Geography**.\n\nTake time to analyze your strengths, interests, and resources before finalizing your optional subject. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
